-- Bunds Slide as Banks Demand Smaller Loans Than Expected From Central Bank
-- Paul Dobson
-- 2010-06-30T09:20:36Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-06-30/bunds-slide-as-banks-demand-smaller-loans-than-expected-from-central-bank.html

          
          
             German government bonds fell after
lenders asked the European Central Bank for 131.9 billion euros
($162 billion) of three-month loans before a 12-month facility
is repaid tomorrow.  
 The yield on the 2-year bond rose three basis points to
0.58 percent as of 10:19 a.m. in London.  
